Underrated car, mainly because of its quirky 80's styling, the cabrio's looked great and fetching big prices today. Later 3.2 and 3.4 litre models were great. The first of the series the Mondial 8 was very underpowered (214bhp) the later quattrovalvole model (4 valves per cylinder) made a big difference, but powerful it was not, 240bhp and weighing in at about 1400 kg, under performer, never built for performance but rather for GT cruising and it was good at that, and had space for 2 kids in the back.
